session.name: Liberty Index 2021 - U.S. House
session.description: Created by the Republican Liberty Caucus, the 2021 Liberty Index is a liberty-focused legislative scorecard for the U.S. House. The Liberty Index scores Republican members of Congress on 20 pivotal bills/votes from 2021 that either advance liberty or diminish liberty.

bills.title: President Biden's budget resolution
bills.description: President Biden's budget resolution.

bills.title: For The People Act of 2021
bills.description: For The People Act of 2021. This would have federalized elections, removing local control and cancelling many state election laws that are crucial for election integrity.

bills.title: Imposes nationwide universal background checks on firearms transfers, which would essentially outlaw private firearm sales/transfers
bills.description: Imposes nationwide universal background checks on firearms transfers, which would essentially outlaw private firearm sales/transfers.

bills.title: The Protecting the Right to Organize Act
bills.description: The Protecting the Right to Organize Act. This violates free market principles by imposing numerous federal regulations on private businesses. It pressures employees of private businesses to pay union fees even if they don't want to join a union, which conflicts with Right to Work laws in 27 states. It also violates worker privacy by mandating that businesses share their employee's personal information with unions.

bills.title: The $1
bills.description: The $1.9 trillion American Rescue Plan Act of 2021.

bills.title: PPP Extension Act of 2021
bills.description: PPP Extension Act of 2021. Extended the Paycheck Protection Program, which bails out businesses with taxpayer funded loans that aren't required to be paid back. Nowhere in the Constitution is the federal government granted this authority. PPP also incentivizes state and local governments to continue their draconian COVID-19 restrictions on businesses.

bills.description: The John R. Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act of 2021. This would have federalized elections, removing local control and cancelling many state election laws that are crucial for election integrity. (Passed 219-212 on 8/24/21).

bills.title: The original draft of the National Defense Authorization Act of 2022
bills.description: The original draft of the National Defense Authorization Act of 2022. Increases military spending to $778 billion, expands the draft by requiring women to register for selective service, permits red-flag gun confiscation for military servicemembers, and includes critical race theory training for military servicemembers.

bills.title: The Immunization Infrastructure Modernization Act of 2021
bills.description: The Immunization Infrastructure Modernization Act of 2021. Expands the CDC and Public Health Department by appropriating an additional $400 million so these bureaucracies can collect additional personal information for their “immunization information systems.”

bills.description: Further Extending Government Funding Act. Funds the federal government through February 18, 2022, which includes funding for Biden's OSHA vaccine mandate.
